# InferTest — expected entailments
# Construct : ClassAssertion over a multi-level subclass hierarchy
#
# Buddy is only asserted a Labrador. A conformant reasoner must type him as
# EVERY ancestor class in the chain (Dog, Mammal, Animal, LivingThing) —
# not just the one directly asserted. Missing any one of these means the
# reasoner (or your pipeline's materialisation step) isn't walking the
# full subclass hierarchy.

@prefix : <http://example.org/infertest#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .

:ClassAssertion_Buddy rdf:type :ClassAssertion_Dog .
:ClassAssertion_Buddy rdf:type :ClassAssertion_Mammal .
:ClassAssertion_Buddy rdf:type :ClassAssertion_Animal .
:ClassAssertion_Buddy rdf:type :ClassAssertion_LivingThing .
